            <strong id="17">So, what's MY ratio?</strong>
            <p>Look at the top of the page under the ADC logo.</p>
            <p>It's important to distinguish between your overall ratio and the individual ratio on each torrent you may be seeding or leeching. The overall ratio takes into account the total uploaded and downloaded from your account since you joined the site. The individual ratio takes into account those values for the <em>current session</em> of each torrent.</p>
            <p>You may see two symbols instead of a number: "Inf.", which is just an abbreviation for Infinity and means that you have downloaded 0 bytes while uploading a non-zero amount (ul/dl becomes infinity); "---", which should be read as "non-available" and shows up when you have both downloaded and uploaded 0 bytes (ul/dl = 0/0 which is an indeterminate amount).</p>
            <br />

            <strong id="67">What is the minimum ratio I need to have?</strong>
            <p>ADC members are required to maintain at least a minimum share ratio, based on their total amount downloaded. It is solely your responsibility to keep yourself above your minimum required ratio.</p>
            <p>A sliding scale is used to calculate your required ratio, based on your total download amount. The more you download, the higher your required ratio becomes, until you reach the cap of <strong>0.5</strong>. No one is required to maintain a higher ratio than 0.5, regardless of how much they have downloaded.</p>
            <p>The sliding scale uses a ratio factor of 200. Your minimum required ratio is calculated by taking your total download amount (in gigabytes) and dividing it by the scale's ratio factor. For example, if you have downloaded 49 GB, your minimum required ratio will be 49 divided by 200, which equals 0.245.</p>
            <p>If you have downloaded less than 15 GB, you do not yet have any ratio requirements to fulfill. But once you reach 15 GB downloaded, the ratio requirements will immediately take effect.</p>
            <p>Failure to meet your required ratio may result in a warning. If you download too much while you are warned, you will have your download privileges removed, and you will then only be able to download golden torrents. Seeding and uploading new torrents will still be possible however.</p>
            <p>Warned users who upload enough to reach their minimum required ratio will have their warning automatically removed in due time. If their download privileges were removed, those privileges will automatically be restored.</p>
            <p>You will never be banned for simply having a bad ratio. Not even if it takes you months to get above your minimum required ratio.</p>
            <br />

            <strong id="18">Why is my IP and email address displayed in my profile?</strong>
            <p>Only you and the site staff can view your IP and email address. That information is not shown to regular users.</p>
            <br />

            <strong id="20">My IP address is dynamic. How do I stay logged in?</strong>
            <p>ADC uses browser cookies to identify you and keep you logged in. As long as you do not logout or delete your cookies, you will be able to view every page on the site without having to login again, even if your IP has changed since your last visit. If you delete your cookies or logout, you will simply need to login again in order to view any pages.</p>
