            <strong id="106">What are bonus points?</strong>
            <p>If you're a member of other private trackers, you are probably at least vaguely familiar with the concept of bonus points. For the uninitiated, a bonus point system essentially allows users to earn points that can be redeemed for various rewards, primarily upload credit. </p>
            <p>In our new system, there are two simple ways to earn bonus points: <strong>1.)</strong> by seeding certain qualifying torrents and <strong>2.)</strong> by actively participating in the community. The purpose of the system is severalfold. First, people often abandon older and less active torrents - or avoid downloading them in the first place - because these torrents generally see far less activity than new torrents. We hope to encourage our members to keep seeding these older and less popular torrents by giving them a small reward for their time and effort. Second, new members often grab torrents which do not present good ratio opportunities, and this results in many of these members experiencing ratio troubles that can best be described as <em>frustrating</em>. Our bonus system provides some alternate routes for them to improve their ratio, while at the same time helping to make ADC a better place for everyone. And finally, while we have a good number of active members who regularly download and seed our DVDs, BDs, and soundtracks, the number who frequently participate in the community is quite a bit lower. So one of our principal goals for the system is to promote a wider range of involvement in the ADC community. This includes uploading torrents, commenting on torrents, posting in our forums, and voting on our polls.</p>
            <p>The system is and always will be a work in progress. We will regularly be adding new rewards, tweaking the mechanics of the system, adjusting the number of points dispensed for the various and sundry activities, and fixing any issues that crop up in the meantime.</p>
            <p>We'll be adding additional rewards in the future, with most of the new rewards targeted at members who do not need a ratio boost. Some of these rewards will only benefit the purchaser, while other rewards will benefit the purchaser as well as other members. So even if you don't find any of the current rewards appealing, you may still want to accumulate points so you can purchase future rewards.</p>
            <p>Note: Asking for other members to send you bonus points anywhere on the site or off the site is not allowed. This includes sending PMs to others asking them to send you points. This behaviour is considered begging for points and it will be met with punishment.</p>
